  "prompt": "Which are the top ninja dragon games?",
  "response": "There are several popular games that feature ninja and dragon elements, combining action, stealth, and fantasy gameplay. Here are some notable titles that fans often consider the top in this genre:\n\n1. **Ninja Gaiden Series**: This classic action-adventure series is known for its fast-paced gameplay, challenging combat, and intricate storylines, often featuring mythical creatures, including dragons.\n\n2. **Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice**: From the creators of Dark Souls, this game features a shinobi protagonist in feudal Japan. While it doesn't have dragons in the traditional sense, it does feature a supernatural theme and powerful bosses.\n\n3. **Dragon Quest XI: Echoes of an Elusive Age**: This RPG incorporates a mix of fantasy elements and includes dragon-themed enemies and characters, along with traditional turn-based combat.\n\n4. **Tenchu Series**: A stealth-oriented series where players take on the role of ninjas. The series features various missions, with some supernatural elements sprinkled throughout.\n\n5. **Nioh Series**: Set in a dark fantasy version of Japan, Nioh includes ninja elements and powerful yokai (including dragon-like creatures) as bosses, combining action RPG mechanics with historical narrative.\n\n6. **Ghost of Tsushima**: While not focused on dragons, it immerses players in the life of a samurai during the Mongol invasion, featuring stealth mechanics similar to those found in ninja games.\n\n7. **Overwatch**: The character Genji is a cybernetic ninja who has dragon-themed ultimate moves (Dragonblade and Dragonblade), adding an intriguing twist to the game.\n\n8. **Shinobi (2002)**: A classic ninja action game featuring multiple bosses, some of which have dragon-like qualities.\n\n9. **Dragon's Crown**: An action RPG with elements of fantasy, including dragons and other mythical creatures, and features characters reminiscent of ninjas.\n\nThese games feature a variety of gameplay styles, from action and stealth to RPG mechanics, and they all include elements of ninjas or dragons in some capacity.",
